                <h1>Engel v. Vitale: Supreme Court's Landmark Ruling on School Prayer</h1>
                <p>Engel v. Vitale was a landmark Supreme Court case decided in 1962 that ruled it unconstitutional for state officials to compose an official school prayer and encourage its recitation in public schools, even if the prayer was nondenominational. The decision emphasized the importance of the separation of church and state in education.</p>
